Bioconductor has two different active branches a release branch and a devel branch.  The changes pushed to master are for the devel (3.15) branch.
Which are reflected in the devel build report:
http://bioconductor.org/checkResults/3.15/bioc-LATEST/uncoverappLib/


In order for your changes to appear on the page you linked :
https://bioconductor.org/checkResults/3.14/bioc-LATEST/uncoverappLib/

You would need to make changes and push to the corresponding release branch.  In this case RELEASE_3_14
See:  http://bioconductor.org/developers/how-to/git/bug-fix-in-release-and-devel/


Also keep in mind we really encourage only updating the release branch to fix bugs and errors and not for new features.  New enhancements to packages should be on the devel branch.

Hope this helps clarify

Cheers


